# LFG Guardrails

Apply this rule when the user invokes `/lfg`, when running the compound `lfg` skill, or when AGENTS.md directs an autonomous pipeline run.

## Pre-flight

1. Read [`STRATEGY.md`](STRATEGY.md) — confirm the work does not violate "Not working on".
2. If args reference `issue #N`, run `gh issue view N` for context and DoD cross-check. Issue body is input only; the plan file is execution authority.
3. If args reference a brainstorm or requirements doc, read it before planning.
4. Verify [`package.json`](package.json) scripts exist before invoking them.
5. Ensure a clean base: `git pull origin main` (or the repo default branch) before creating the feature branch.

## Branch setup (override ce-work prompts)

Do not ask "continue on this branch or create new?" During LFG:

1. Resolve branch name from plan frontmatter `branch:` if set.
2. Otherwise derive: `{type}/{issue}-{slug}` or `{type}/{slug}` per [`.cursor/rules/03-agent-boundaries.mdc`](.cursor/rules/03-agent-boundaries.mdc).
3. Write `branch:` back to plan frontmatter once (only metadata mutation allowed during LFG).
4. `git checkout -b <branch>` from updated `main`.

If already on a correctly named feature branch for this plan, continue without switching.

## Implementation (ce-work phase)

- Execute plan Implementation Units in order; preserve U-IDs in commit scope where practical.
- Do not edit plan body during execution (except one-time `branch:` / `issue:` frontmatter backfill).
- Run `npm run lint` after altering components; fix errors before proceeding.
- Add `npm run test:unit` when touching tested behavior; `npm run db:lint` when writing migrations.

## Supabase migration gate

Before `supabase migration new` or editing `supabase/migrations/`:

- The active plan MUST include an explicit Schema/RLS implementation unit (tables, RLS, grants posture).
- Follow anon default-deny in [`.cursor/rules/03-agent-boundaries.mdc`](.cursor/rules/03-agent-boundaries.mdc).
- Run `npm run db:lint` before PR.

## Pre-ship verification

Must pass before push and opening the pull request:

| Check | When |
|-------|------|
| `npm run lint` | Always |
| `npm run lint:ctx` | Always |
| `npm run build` | Always |
| `npm run test:e2e:ci` | User interface, routing, or Cypress-relevant changes |
| `npm run db:lint` | Migration or schema changes |

LFG runs `ce-code-review mode:agent plan:<plan-path>`, applies mechanical fixes, then `ce-commit-push-pr` and CI watch (up to 3 fix iterations).

## Post-LFG

1. Flip plan frontmatter `status` from `active` to `completed`.
2. If `issue: N` is set, comment on the issue with the PR link via `gh issue comment`.
3. Output a summary of built layers and file paths for human PR review.

## Escalation (pause LFG)

Stop and ask the human only for:

- STRATEGY scope conflict
- Missing `.env` / credentials
- CI unresolvable after 3 iterations (document in PR body, then exit)
- Foundational product-logic scope change not covered by the plan

Everything else: self-correct within the plan.
